    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-02-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-02-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="68"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d68">
                <head>68. Message to Athens<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d68fn1">Source:
                        Department of State, <gloss target="#t_NEA1">NEA</gloss> Files: Lot 59 D
                        518, Alpha—<persName corresp="#p_AD1">Anderson</persName> Talks w/<gloss
                            target="#t_BG1">BG</gloss> &amp; <persName corresp="#p_NNNCGA1"
                            >Nasser</persName>. Jan.’56—memos, etc. Secret. Repeated to
                        Washington.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 70</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-02-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 2, 1956</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Since … meetings with <persName corresp="#p_BER1">Black</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_NNNCGA1">Nasr</persName>,<note n="2" xml:id="d68fn2">See <ref
                            target="#d62">Document 62</ref> and <ref target="#d67">
                            <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>
                        </ref>
                    </note> high dam talks have taken turn for better with both sides giving ground.
                    Have now agreed exchange letters of commitment and Egyptians agree accept <gloss
                        target="#t_IBRD1">IBRD</gloss> terms with “appropriate” competitive bidding.
                    Understanding include delay commencement major work until Nile waters agreement.
                    Both sides now optimistic. <persName corresp="#p_BER1">Black</persName> expects
                    remain until about 8 February.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
